The `overallArgValues` is supposed to hold a GCP project ID, GCS staging bucket, and soon-to-be-introduced Google account email. `defaultOptionsComponent` is the UI part that contains these values. However, as can be seen above, `overallArgValues` is initialized only when `isUseDefaultOptions` is true (when a user decides to use values defined in the current launch configuration which will override project-wide or workspace-wide values). I think we should initialize the `overallArgValues` too when `isUseDefaultOptions` is false, with the values from a project or a workspace.

